eldr — NOTICE

Third-party provenance and acknowledgements.

eldr has zero build or runtime dependencies: `Cargo.lock` contains exactly one
package (eldr), and every OS binding is hand-written `extern "C"` FFI declared by
eldr itself. The projects below were studied as references while re-deriving that
FFI from Apple's framework interfaces. None of them is linked, vendored, or
otherwise depended on.

FFI provenance
--------------
macmon — https://github.com/vladkens/macmon
  Copyright (c) vladkens. Licensed under the MIT License.
  Reference for the IOReport key map (package/CPU/GPU/ANE power, per-cluster
  frequency residencies), the AppleSMC access pattern (fan + temperature keys),
  and the host/mach memory accounting.

freedomtan/sensors — https://github.com/freedomtan/sensors
  Reference for reading AppleVendor IOHID temperature sensors without sudo.

These acknowledgements concern reference material only and do not alter eldr's
own license (MIT — see LICENSE).
